 172-207 in make poision by working with ONLY spirit of sloth, and farming the stuff for the first 200 sealed vials.  It cost me 5Kpp.  After the 200 vials were up I just bought vials from Brak.  With an charisma of 65, wis of 80, and intel of 75.  The components cost me about 1pp more than the sell back value without any failed attempts.  At skill 207 I have about a 55% success ratio with spirit of sloth.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hokksin<br>
56th Rogue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uronax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ronax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/9/01 2:36:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The True Cost of poision from skill 172-207</span><hr size=1> I can vouch for that info.  I have recently gone from 163 to 193 using only my own made vials, also 200.  Have spent around 3500 plat.  Have to say though, that having a cha so low is really hurtin the bottom line.  I think my cha is 115 or so with 3 items that I swap in for merchants, mask of deception +7, crude stien +10?(replace Bloodpoint to drop neg cha), and drake hide legs +5.  Yeah, it looks dumb, but I get better selling price and buying price. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usnarkystabwell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snarky Stabwell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/15/01 7:49:56 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The True Cost of poision from skill 172-207</span><hr size=1> I recommend you make a shopping mule enchanter, use an illusion and the spell alliance on the trader and shop at the cheapest possible prices. <br>
<br>
It DOES pay off really quickly and the chanter can serve as a storage mule for poison ingredients while he is not needed for shopping. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Profile=0&Id=66447">Snarky Stabwell</a>
<br>59th Epic Blackguard
<br><a href="http://62.13.10.213/landslide">Landslide</a> -Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilvorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/15/01 8:50:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The True Cost of poision from skill 172-207</span><hr size=1> I spent approx 7k going from 109 to 250. Used about 100 sealed vials I made. Bought the rest. Did nothing but spirit of the sloth because it was easy to sit in one spot. My advice get cha gear and use it when buying and selling poisons back.<br>
Get INT gear it helps a LOT. Right now I can get my base 75 int doubled to 150. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uanariak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anariak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="                                                                  http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/15/01 11:27:51 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The True Cost of poision from skill 172-207</span><hr size=1> while it is time consuming it is best to make the vials yourself, costs about 2pp per vial insetad of 6, now that all animal skins are stackable you can go around killin stuff in newbie zones while aucting for skins as well, doesnt take long to get all the skins you need for the vials <p>Glad to Rake your aquaintance         
